
We like to classify anything: A, B and C customers; low-, medium- and high-risk credit risk applicants, species, races.
We want to know if an email is spam or not? This is a typical classification for eMails.

Classification assigns an item (»object«) to a set of predefined classes.

If there is no set of predefined classes, we talk of → development/Data/mining/Clustering[clustering].

Techniques: Decision trees, nearest neighbour, neural networks, link analysis.

sa:
  → development/Data/mining/Estimation

  → development/Data/pattern-identification
